**Sets in Python**
--> unordered and unique collectn of elts
--> automatically remove duplicates and are great for mathematical operations
1. Creating a Set
fruits = {"apple", "banana", "cherry"}
print(fruits)
Duplicates are ignored;
nums = {1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 4}
print(nums)    => {1, 2, 3, 4}
2. Adding & Removing Elements
--> .add()
--> .remove() and .discard()
3. Set Operations (Math Style!)
print(A | B)   => Union -- all elts in A and B
print(A & B)   => Intersection -- common elts b/w A and B
print(A - B)   => Difference -- elts in A
print(A ^ B)   => Symmetric difference -- except common elts
4. Other Useful Methods
print(len())       => number of items
.clear()           => remove all
